  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200&deg;C/ 180&deg;C (fan)/ 400&deg;F/ Gas 6</p>\r\n<p>Pat the <strong>pork belly</strong> dry with kitchen paper</p>\r\n<p>Score the <strong>fatty side</strong> of the<strong> pork belly</strong> in a criss-cross pattern by drawing a sharp knife through the skin, deep enough to reach the meat below</p>\r\n<p>Season with a very generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and rub it deep into the criss-cross pattern</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-asian-pork-belly-noodle-salad/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a very high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once very hot, add the <strong>pork belly</strong>, fat side down and cook for 4 min or until coloured and crispy, then flip and cook for 2 min on the other side&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once done, transfer the <strong>pork</strong> to a <strong>tin foil</strong> lined baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 40 min</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-asian-pork-belly-noodle-salad/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>wholewheat noodles</strong> to a pot and cover with <strong>boiled water</strong> until fully submerged</p>\r\n<p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 5-7 min or until tender with a slight bite, then drain and run under <strong>cold water</strong> until cooled</p>\r\n<p>Once cooled, set aside for later</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-asian-pork-belly-noodle-salad/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine the <strong>chilli jam</strong>&nbsp;with 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> <strong>soy sauce sachets </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)<strong>&nbsp;</strong>in a small bowl &ndash; this is your <strong>pork glaze</strong></p>\r\n<p>Bash the <strong>roasted peanuts</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> until they are finely crushed (keep them in the bag so you don't lose any!)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-asian-pork-belly-noodle-salad/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine the <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>rice vinegar</strong>, remaining <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>toasted sesame oil</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>&ndash;&nbsp;this is your&nbsp;<strong>dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-asian-pork-belly-noodle-salad/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rip the <strong>little gem<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;and chop the <strong>cucumber</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Trim, then slice the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>finely</p>\r\n<p>Top, tail, peel and grate the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Pick the <strong>coriander</strong> and <strong>mint leaves</strong> from the stalks and chop them roughly</p>\r\n<p>Cut the <strong>red&nbsp;chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> in half lengthways, de-seed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop into thin strips</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-asian-pork-belly-noodle-salad/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add all of the above to a large salad bowl with the <strong>cooled noodles</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once the <strong>pork</strong> has had&nbsp;40 min, remove the tray from the oven and spoon over the<strong>&nbsp;pork glaze</strong></p>\r\n<p>Sprinkle over the&nbsp;<strong>crushed peanuts</strong> and return the tray to the oven for 5-7 min (scrunch the foil edges up to stop the glaze escaping!)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-asian-pork-belly-noodle-salad/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once done, remove the <strong>pork</strong> from the oven, leave to rest for 5 min, then slice it finely</p>\r\n<p>Dress the <strong>noodle salad</strong> with the <strong>dressing</strong></p>\r\n<p>Serve the<strong> sticky Asian pork</strong> over the <strong>noodle salad </strong>and drizzle with any remaining <strong>glaze</strong>&nbsp;and <strong>crushed</strong> <strong>nuts</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
